President Biden addressed the press in the Roosevelt Room, discussing student debt relief and the recent events in Congress. He emphasized the need to work together and change the toxic atmosphere in Washington. Regarding student debt relief, Biden highlighted the reforms made to the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program and the Income-Driven Repayment program. He announced that his administration has approved an additional $9 billion in relief for 125,000 borrowers, bringing the total student debt cancellation to $127 billion for nearly 3.6 million Americans. Biden also mentioned his administration's efforts to provide relief through the Higher Education Act, despite facing opposition from Republicans and special interests. He expressed his commitment to easing the burden of student debt and helping Americans achieve their dreams. In response to questions, Biden discussed his relationship with Speaker McCarthy, concerns about delivering aid to Ukraine, and the upcoming speech he plans to make on the importance of supporting Ukraine.